<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="517" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d517">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/924.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Chargé <persName type="to">Terres</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 18, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Legation’s May 10. Inform Livingston that he is authorized to proceed to
                            Ouanaminthe with the Bishop of Cape Haitien and may employ his good
                            offices with a view to making peace between the Government and leaders
                            of the revolution.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>